Add your design elements. The water pump should remain accessible for adjustment, repair and cleaning, either by leaving an opening or door, or with easy disassembly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fc/Make-an-Outdoor-Fountain-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-an-Outdoor-Fountain-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/fc/Make-an-Outdoor-Fountain-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-557px-Make-an-Outdoor-Fountain-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":462,"bigWidth":"558","bigHeight":"560","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
